se yet emotionally charged and passionate piano solos are embedded in sine waves or reworked to establish new aesthetics of piano sound. Sparse percussions and throbbing bass pulses hover above and below – the music being contemplative and minimal at the same time.\n\nThe tracks \"Microon\" I-III contain recordings of one of the 15 pianos using a 16th tone interval tuning built by Sauter, Spaichingen/Donaueschingen, Germany. The original \"piano metamorfoseador en dieciseisavos de tono\" was designed by Julián Carrillo Trujillo. Thanks to the music department of Bern University of the Arts for making this instrument available. Included in the album are two cover versions of the track \"By This River\", originally written by Roedelius, Moebius and Brian Eno in 1977. In their instrumental versions of the song Nicolai and Sakamoto create and investigate the song's appeal in both normal speed and slow motion. <a href=\"http://www.last.fm/music/Alva+Noto+%252B+Ryuichi+Sakamoto/Summvs\">Read more on Last.fm</a>. User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License; additional terms may apply."}}}